<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/>kopparake<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>ripa<unclear>ṉma</unclear>kku yāṇṭu 8 Āvatu vaṭakarai miṟaikkūṟṟattu <hi rend="grantha">brahmade</hi>yam <unclear>ti</unclear>ru<note>SII reads<hi rend="grantha">vica</hi> after <hi rend="grantha">tiru</hi>. However, I could not see any letters.</note>
<lb n="2"/>lūr vārakkiyaṉ Iravi vaṭukaṉṉu Ivaṉ <unclear>ṟa</unclear>mpi Iravi tattaṉum Ivviruv<unclear>o</unclear><note>We see only the left part of the –<hi rend="grantha">o</hi>. SII adds an -<hi rend="grantha">m</hi> at the end, but there is no space for it.</note>
<lb n="3"/>kuṉṟakūṟṟattu<hi rend="grantha">brahmade</hi>yamc ciṟupaḻuvūr ma<unclear>ṟa</unclear>
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>This is the 8th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. We two <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivviruvō</foreign><supplied reason="lost"><foreign>m</foreign></supplied></supplied>, Vārakkiyaṉ Iravi Vaṭukaṉ and his younger brother <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivaṉ ṟampi &gt;</foreign> <foreign>ivaṉ tampi</foreign></supplied> Iravi Tattaṉ, of Tiru<supplied reason="lost">nal</supplied>lūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Miṟaikkūṟṟam on the northern bank, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Maṟava<supplied reason="lost">ṉīśvara</supplied> of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> in Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>

